class main.core.query_generation.strategies.aggregation_query_strategy.AggregationQueryStrategy¶

Bases: BaseQueryStrategy

generate_query(schema_metadata, db_type: str, selector: int = None) → str¶

Generate a SQL query based on the schema metadata and target database type.

Parameters: - schema_metadata: SQLAlchemy MetaData object representing the DB schema - db_type: The target DB type (e.g., “mysql”, “postgresql”) - selector: An optional integer seed used to produce predictable variations of queries.

If not provided, a random number is used to introduce variety.

Returns: A valid SQL query string
